{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# In sixteen hundred seven #

3
00:00:16,510 --> 00:00:19,310
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# We sailed the open sea #

4
00:00:19,350 --> 00:00:21,580
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# For glory, God and gold #

5
00:00:21,620 --> 00:00:24,810
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# and the Virginia Company #

6
00:00:24,850 --> 00:00:27,350
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# For the New World is like heaven #

7
00:00:27,390 --> 00:00:30,190
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# And we'll all be rich and free #

8
00:00:30,230 --> 00:00:32,390
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Or so we have been told #

9
00:00:32,430 --> 00:00:36,020
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# by the Virginia Company #

10
00:00:36,070 --> 00:00:38,090
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# So we have been told #

11
00:00:38,130 --> 00:00:41,500
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# by the Virginia Company #

12
00:00:51,750 --> 00:00:54,010
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# For glory, God and gold #

13
00:00:54,050 --> 00:00:57,510
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# and the Virginia Company #

14
00:00:57,550 --> 00:01:00,180
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Ready to hoist the cannon? - Right!

15
00:01:00,220 --> 00:01:01,780
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hey, look. Is that Smith?

16
00:01:01,820 --> 00:01:03,950
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's him, all right. The old sea dog.

17
00:01:03,990 --> 00:01:05,430
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Captain John Smith?

18
00:01:05,460 --> 00:01:07,290
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I've heard some amazing stories about him.

19
00:01:07,330 --> 00:01:09,520
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Are you coming on this voyage too?

20
00:01:09,570 --> 00:01:11,530
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Of course he is, you half-wit!

21
00:01:11,570 --> 00:01:13,800
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You can't fight Indians without John Smith.

22
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:15,000
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's right.

23
00:01:15,040 --> 00:01:17,270
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm not about to let you boys have all the fun.

24
00:01:18,610 --> 00:01:21,410
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# On the beaches of Virginny #

25
00:01:21,440 --> 00:01:24,140
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# There's diamonds like debris #

26
00:01:24,180 --> 00:01:26,650
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# There silver rivers flow #

27
00:01:26,680 --> 00:01:29,710
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# and gold you pick right off a tree #

28
00:01:29,750 --> 00:01:31,780
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# With a nugget for my Winnie #

29
00:01:31,820 --> 00:01:34,650
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# And another one for me #

30
00:01:34,690 --> 00:01:36,820
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# And all the rest will #

31
00:01:36,860 --> 00:01:40,160
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# go to the Virginia Company #

32
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,790
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# To glory, God and gold #

33
00:01:42,830 --> 00:01:49,570
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# And the Virginia Company #

34
00:01:53,810 --> 00:01:55,300
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Haul on the brace!

35
00:01:56,550 --> 00:01:58,170
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come on, come on!

36
00:01:58,210 --> 00:02:00,180
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Do your best!

37
00:02:00,220 --> 00:02:01,510
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Watch out!

38
00:02:05,550 --> 00:02:07,820
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Faster! She's taking on more water!

39
00:02:11,730 --> 00:02:13,850
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look out!

40
00:02:17,230 --> 00:02:19,790
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}John! Get down here!

41
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:22,100
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The cannons are breaking loose!

42
00:02:25,810 --> 00:02:27,970
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Reef the topsails! - Yes, sir!

43
00:02:28,010 --> 00:02:29,570
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Steady on your course.

44
00:02:29,610 --> 00:02:32,640
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's all right, Thomas. We'll get her tied off.

45
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:33,980
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Say your prayers, men!

46
00:02:43,030 --> 00:02:44,890
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thomas, watch it!

47
00:02:49,370 --> 00:02:51,490
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Help!

48
00:02:51,530 --> 00:02:53,400
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Man overboard!

49
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:54,600
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Help!

50
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:56,570
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Stay your course! He's lost!

51
00:02:56,610 --> 00:02:57,830
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Help!

52
00:02:57,870 --> 00:03:00,810
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Pull the pins! - Aye, sir!

53
00:03:04,650 --> 00:03:06,670
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Smith!

54
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:08,110
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Smith!

55
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:11,540
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Are you crazy?

56
00:03:12,820 --> 00:03:15,090
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hang on, Thomas! I've got you!

57
00:03:18,060 --> 00:03:19,360
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Quick! The rope!

58
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:22,660
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Heave!

59
00:03:27,740 --> 00:03:29,860
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come on, lads! Pull!

60
00:03:32,410 --> 00:03:34,500
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pull! Pull!

61
00:03:34,540 --> 00:03:36,240
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Put your back into it!

62
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:39,180
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Pull! - Pull! Pull!

63
00:03:39,220 --> 00:03:40,580
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hang on!

64
00:03:43,290 --> 00:03:44,780
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There, my lucky lads!

65
00:03:46,790 --> 00:03:49,550
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, that was refreshing.

66
00:03:49,590 --> 00:03:51,490
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well done, Smith.

67
00:03:51,530 --> 00:03:53,090
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Of course,

68
00:03:53,130 --> 00:03:54,690
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}you'd all do the same for me.

69
00:03:54,730 --> 00:03:56,660
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Oh, sure, sure. - Of course we would.

70
00:03:56,700 --> 00:03:58,000
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Sure, yes! - Yeah, we would!

71
00:03:58,030 --> 00:03:59,860
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Absolutely!

72
00:04:01,300 --> 00:04:03,270
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Trouble on deck?

73
00:04:03,310 --> 00:04:04,600
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Governor Ratcliffe!

74
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:06,270
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thomas fell overboard, sir.

75
00:04:06,310 --> 00:04:08,440
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thank heavens he's been successfully retrieved.

76
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:10,950
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Well done, Smith. - Thank you, sir.

77
00:04:10,980 --> 00:04:12,780
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't lose heart, men.

78
00:04:12,820 --> 00:04:15,280
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It won't be long before we reach the New World...

79
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:18,450
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And remember what awaits us there...

80
00:04:18,490 --> 00:04:20,250
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Freedom...

81
00:04:20,290 --> 00:04:21,980
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}prosperity...

82
00:04:22,020 --> 00:04:24,050
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}the adventure of our lives.

83
00:04:24,090 --> 00:04:26,720
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're the finest crew England has to offer...

84
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:29,060
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and nothing... not wind nor rain

85
00:04:29,100 --> 00:04:31,070
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}nor a thousand bloodthirsty savages

86
00:04:31,100 --> 00:04:33,030
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}shall stand in our way.

87
00:04:33,070 --> 00:04:34,430
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Carry on, men!

88
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:38,600
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}A stirring oration, sir.

89
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:41,510
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm sure the men were most exhilarated!

90
00:04:41,540 --> 00:04:42,840
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Let us hope so.

91
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:47,250
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll need those witless peasants to dig up my gold, won't I?

92
00:04:48,650 --> 00:04:51,620
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This New World's gonna be great, John.

93
00:04:51,650 --> 00:04:53,950
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm gonna get a pile of gold...

94
00:04:53,990 --> 00:04:55,620
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}build me a big house...

95
00:04:55,660 --> 00:04:58,630
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and if any Indian tries to stop me, I'll blast him.

96
00:04:58,660 --> 00:05:01,290
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You just worry about that fortune of yours, Thomas.

97
00:05:01,330 --> 00:05:02,700
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Leave the savages to me.

98
00:05:02,730 --> 00:05:04,460
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You think they'll give us much trouble?

99
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:07,560
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Not as much trouble as Smith'll give them.

100
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,900
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# We'll kill ourselves an Injun #

101
00:05:09,940 --> 00:05:12,570
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Or maybe two or three #

102
00:05:12,610 --> 00:05:15,100
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# We're stalwart men and bold #

103
00:05:15,140 --> 00:05:18,050
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# of the Virginia Company #

104
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:20,110
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What do you suppose the New World will look like?

105
00:05:20,150 --> 00:05:21,640
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Like all the others, I suppose.

106
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:25,250
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I've seen hundreds of new worlds, Thomas.

107
00:05:25,290 --> 00:05:28,420
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What could possibly be different about this one?

108
00:05:28,460 --> 00:05:29,490
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# It's glory, God and gold #

109
00:05:29,490 --> 00:05:30,980
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# It's glory, God and gold #

110
00:05:31,030 --> 00:05:36,860
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# And the Virginia Company #

111
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:19,000
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Steady as the beating drum #

112
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:21,640
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Singing to the cedar flute #

113
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:24,010
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Seasons go and seasons come #

114
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:28,350
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Bring the corn and bear the fruit #

115
00:06:28,380 --> 00:06:30,410
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# By the waters sweet and clean #

116
00:06:30,450 --> 00:06:32,940
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Where the mighty sturgeon lives #

117
00:06:32,990 --> 00:06:35,290
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Plant the squash and reap the bean #

118
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:39,260
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# All the Earth our mother gives #

119
00:06:39,290 --> 00:06:41,730
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Oh, great spirit, hear our song #

120
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:44,130
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Help us keep the ancient ways #

121
00:06:44,170 --> 00:06:46,570
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Keep the sacred fire strong #

122
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:50,700
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Walk in balance all our days #

123
00:06:50,740 --> 00:06:52,930
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Seasons go and seasons come #

124
00:06:52,980 --> 00:06:55,440
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# steady as the beating drum #

125
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:57,310
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Plum to seed to bud to plum #

126
00:07:02,250 --> 00:07:04,190
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Steady as the beating drum #

127
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:23,130
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's good to be home.

128
00:07:24,970 --> 00:07:27,600
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The Massawomecks are defeated!

129
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:29,610
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}With the help of our brothers,

130
00:07:29,650 --> 00:07:32,240
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}our villages are safe again.

131
00:07:34,050 --> 00:07:37,680
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Your return has brought much joy to the village.

132
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:41,120
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look at all the smiling faces.

133
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:44,460
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes, but there's one smiling face I don't see.

134
00:07:44,490 --> 00:07:46,360
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Where is my daughter?

135
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:47,950
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You know Pocahontas.

136
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,290
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She has her mother's spirit.

137
00:07:50,330 --> 00:07:52,960
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}She goes wherever the wind takes her.

138
00:08:11,550 --> 00:08:14,020
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas!

139
00:08:14,060 --> 00:08:16,420
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Your father's back!

140
00:08:16,460 --> 00:08:18,360
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come down here!

141
00:08:18,390 --> 00:08:21,230
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's back, Flit.

142
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:25,790
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come on, Meeko!

143
00:08:33,540 --> 00:08:36,410
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No! Not that way.

144
00:08:45,490 --> 00:08:47,510
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Show-off.

