{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# You will understand #

288
00:17:40,660 --> 00:17:44,280
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Let it break upon you #

289
00:17:44,330 --> 00:17:47,260
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Like a wave upon the sand #

290
00:17:47,300 --> 00:17:49,460
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's saying something's coming.

291
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:51,020
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Strange clouds?

292
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:54,400
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Listen with your heart #

293
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:58,240
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# You will understand #

294
00:18:04,150 --> 00:18:06,770
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What do you see?

295
00:18:06,820 --> 00:18:09,080
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Clouds.

296
00:18:09,120 --> 00:18:11,850
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Strange clouds.

297
00:18:13,790 --> 00:18:16,550
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look at it, Wiggins...

298
00:18:16,590 --> 00:18:20,290
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}An entire new world chock full of gold...

299
00:18:20,330 --> 00:18:22,460
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}just waiting for me.

300
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:26,260
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And scores of adventures waiting for us. Right, Percy?

301
00:18:26,300 --> 00:18:28,740
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Do you think we'll meet some savages?

302
00:18:28,770 --> 00:18:30,430
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}If we do, we shall be sure...

303
00:18:30,470 --> 00:18:31,800
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}to give them a proper English greeting.

304
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:33,740
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Ooh! gift baskets!

305
00:18:33,780 --> 00:18:37,270
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, no! And he came so highly recommended.

306
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:40,910
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's perfect, Governor.

307
00:18:40,950 --> 00:18:43,820
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The water's deep enough. We can pull right up to shore.

308
00:18:43,850 --> 00:18:45,080
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hey there, Percy.

309
00:18:47,060 --> 00:18:48,520
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Very well, then. Give the order.

310
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:49,780
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Already done, sir.

311
00:18:49,820 --> 00:18:51,660
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I've got a crew assembled and they're ready to go.

312
00:18:51,690 --> 00:18:53,130
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}About the natives...

313
00:18:53,160 --> 00:18:55,130
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm counting on you to make sure...

314
00:18:55,160 --> 00:18:57,790
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}those filthy heathens don't disrupt our mission.

315
00:18:57,830 --> 00:19:00,670
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, if they're anything like the savages I've fought before,

316
00:19:00,700 --> 00:19:02,260
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}it's nothing I can't handle.

317
00:19:02,300 --> 00:19:05,430
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Right. That'll be all, Smith. - There's a good man.

318
00:19:05,470 --> 00:19:06,910
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}See you, Percy.

319
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:11,910
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The men like Smith, don't they?

320
00:19:13,980 --> 00:19:17,080
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I've never been... a popular man.

321
00:19:17,120 --> 00:19:18,350
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I like you.

322
00:19:18,390 --> 00:19:19,910
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And don't think I don't know...

323
00:19:19,950 --> 00:19:22,250
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}what those back stabbers at court say about me.

324
00:19:22,290 --> 00:19:23,920
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, yes, all that talk about

325
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:25,950
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}being a pathetic social climber who's failed at everything...

326
00:19:25,990 --> 00:19:29,590
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm very well aware that this is my last chance for glory.

327
00:19:29,630 --> 00:19:31,120
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But mark my words, Wiggins.

328
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:33,930
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}When King James sees the gold these peasants unearth...

329
00:19:33,970 --> 00:19:38,230
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}success will be mine at last.

330
00:19:39,470 --> 00:19:41,770
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Wake up! Shake a leg!

331
00:19:41,810 --> 00:19:43,670
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's incredible!

332
00:19:43,710 --> 00:19:45,410
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And it's all ours.

333
00:19:45,450 --> 00:19:47,180
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I've never seen anything like it.

334
00:19:47,220 --> 00:19:49,740
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It could look like Ratcliffe's knickers, for all I care...

335
00:19:49,780 --> 00:19:52,410
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}just as long as I get off this stinkin' boat.

336
00:19:52,450 --> 00:19:53,610
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come on, men.

337
00:19:53,660 --> 00:19:55,890
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We didn't come all this way just to look at it.

338
00:20:50,580 --> 00:20:56,070
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Keep it taut, lads. Keep it taut. Steady! Steady! Hold up! That's far enough.

339
00:20:56,920 --> 00:20:59,080
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All right... now. Tie her off.

340
00:20:59,120 --> 00:21:01,210
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Here, John, tie off this end.

341
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:03,750
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}John? John?

342
00:21:03,790 --> 00:21:06,420
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What are you doing up there?

343
00:21:06,460 --> 00:21:08,760
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Getting a better look.

344
00:21:39,530 --> 00:21:43,830
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You're a strange-looking fellow.

345
00:21:43,870 --> 00:21:45,360
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Are you hungry?

346
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:47,600
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Here you go. Ah, it's a biscuit.

347
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:51,400
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's food. Well, sort of.

348
00:21:52,540 --> 00:21:54,510
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You like it, eh?

349
00:21:54,540 --> 00:21:57,640
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, try eating it for four months straight.

350
00:22:01,350 --> 00:22:02,980
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You got a friend back there?

351
00:22:13,360 --> 00:22:16,800
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hey! Wh... What? Watch out.

352
00:22:18,570 --> 00:22:20,360
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What? Get... No, get... Uh, look out.

353
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:22,630
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}John, you better get down here!

354
00:22:22,670 --> 00:22:24,500
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The governor's coming ashore.

355
00:22:24,540 --> 00:22:27,130
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All right. All right. I'm leaving.

356
00:22:44,530 --> 00:22:47,550
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Did you see their skin? They have hair on their faces like dogs.

357
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:52,000
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}My brothers, we must know more about these visitors.

358
00:22:52,030 --> 00:22:55,000
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kekata, what do you see?

359
00:23:11,120 --> 00:23:14,610
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}These are not men like us...

360
00:23:14,660 --> 00:23:19,490
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}but strange beasts with bodies that shine like the sun...

361
00:23:19,530 --> 00:23:23,590
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and weapons that spout fire and thunder.

362
00:23:27,900 --> 00:23:31,500
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They prowl the Earth like ravenous wolves...

363
00:23:31,540 --> 00:23:34,010
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}consuming everything in their path.

364
00:23:39,510 --> 00:23:41,950
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Great Powhatan, I will lead our warriors

365
00:23:41,980 --> 00:23:43,140
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}to the river and attack.

366
00:23:43,180 --> 00:23:44,550
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We will destroy these invaders...

367
00:23:44,590 --> 00:23:47,490
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}the way we destroyed the Massawomecks.

368
00:23:47,520 --> 00:23:50,860
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kocoum, in that battle we knew how to fight our enemy...

369
00:23:50,890 --> 00:23:53,550
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But these pale visitors are strange to us.

370
00:23:53,590 --> 00:23:56,090
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Take some men to the river to observe them.

371
00:23:56,130 --> 00:23:58,790
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Let us hope they do not intend to stay.

372
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:03,270
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I hereby claim this land and all its riches...

373
00:24:03,300 --> 00:24:06,240
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}in the name of His Majesty King James the First...

374
00:24:06,270 --> 00:24:10,010
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and do so name this settlement Jamestown.

375
00:24:11,280 --> 00:24:14,840
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Bravo! Bravo! Beautifully spoken, sir!

376
00:24:14,880 --> 00:24:16,210
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hurry now, Percy.

377
00:24:16,250 --> 00:24:19,120
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We must be all squeaky clean for the New World.

378
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:03,190
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Captain Smith,

379
00:25:03,230 --> 00:25:06,000
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}it appears I've selected the perfect location, eh?

380
00:25:06,030 --> 00:25:07,230
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Not a savage in sight.

381
00:25:07,270 --> 00:25:08,460
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Just because we don't see them...

382
00:25:08,500 --> 00:25:10,160
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}doesn't mean they're not out there, sir.

383
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:12,600
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, then perhaps you should venture forth...

384
00:25:12,640 --> 00:25:16,370
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and determine their whereabouts, hmm?

385
00:25:16,410 --> 00:25:18,900
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}If there are any Indians out there, I'll find them.

386
00:25:21,950 --> 00:25:23,440
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Now, gentlemen, to work.

387
00:25:23,480 --> 00:25:25,280
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- You men, get the ship unloaded. - Right, sir.

388
00:25:25,320 --> 00:25:26,650
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You men, build the fort.

389
00:25:26,690 --> 00:25:29,420
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The rest of you, break out the shovels!

390
00:25:29,460 --> 00:25:31,290
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's time to start digging!

391
00:25:31,330 --> 00:25:32,590
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Digging? - Digging?

392
00:25:32,630 --> 00:25:33,920
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why, of course!

393
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:35,950
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Let's not forget what the Spanish found...

394
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:37,790
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}when they came to the New World.

395
00:25:37,830 --> 00:25:41,200
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Gold! Mountains of it.

396
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:44,640
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Why, for years they've been ravaging the New World...

397
00:25:44,670 --> 00:25:46,900
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}of its most precious resources...

398
00:25:46,940 --> 00:25:48,930
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}but now...

399
00:25:50,780 --> 00:25:53,410
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}it's our turn.

400
00:25:53,450 --> 00:25:55,470
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# The gold of Cortez #

401
00:25:55,520 --> 00:25:57,480
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# The jewels of Pizarro #

402
00:25:57,520 --> 00:25:59,540
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Will seem like mere trinkets #

403
00:25:59,590 --> 00:26:01,580
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# by this time tomorrow #

404
00:26:01,620 --> 00:26:03,590
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# The gold we find here #

405
00:26:03,620 --> 00:26:05,460
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# will dwarf them by far #

406
00:26:05,490 --> 00:26:08,430
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Oh, with all you got in ya, boys #

407
00:26:08,460 --> 00:26:12,460
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Dig up Virginia, boys #

408
00:26:12,500 --> 00:26:14,230
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Mine, boys #

409
00:26:14,270 --> 00:26:15,740
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Mine every mountain

410
00:26:15,770 --> 00:26:17,360
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# And dig, boys #

411
00:26:17,410 --> 00:26:19,070
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Dig 'til you drop #

412
00:26:19,110 --> 00:26:20,700
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Grab a pick, boys #

413
00:26:20,740 --> 00:26:22,610
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Quick, boys #

414
00:26:22,640 --> 00:26:24,110
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Shove in a shovel #

415
00:26:24,150 --> 00:26:26,810
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Uncover those loverly pebbles #

416
00:26:26,850 --> 00:26:28,640
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# that sparkle and shine #

417
00:26:28,680 --> 00:26:31,310
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# It's gold #

418
00:26:31,350 --> 00:26:32,790
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# and it's mine #

419
00:26:32,820 --> 00:26:34,080
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Mine, #

420
00:26:34,120 --> 00:26:35,650
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# mine #

421
00:26:35,690 --> 00:26:38,060
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Dig and dig and diggety dig #

422
00:26:38,090 --> 00:26:40,620
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# And dig and dig and diggety dig #

423
00:26:42,130 --> 00:26:43,790
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Ooh, how I love it. #

424
00:26:45,300 --> 00:26:46,930
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Riches for cheap. #

425
00:26:48,500 --> 00:26:49,970
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# There'll be heaps of it. #

426
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:53,370
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# And I'll be on top of the heap. #

427
00:26:53,410 --> 00:26:55,000
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Diggety, diggety, dig #

428
00:26:55,040 --> 00:26:56,740
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# My rivals back home #

