{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, he's gone.

717
00:45:06,770 --> 00:45:09,860
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Aye. Your singing must have scared them off.

718
00:45:09,900 --> 00:45:11,530
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, then go get him, for heaven's sake!

719
00:45:11,570 --> 00:45:13,400
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What if we run into the Indians?

720
00:45:13,440 --> 00:45:16,240
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's what guns are for.

721
00:45:16,280 --> 00:45:18,570
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Now arm yourselves and get moving!

722
00:45:44,000 --> 00:45:45,970
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas.

723
00:45:46,010 --> 00:45:48,940
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You should be inside the village.

724
00:45:48,980 --> 00:45:50,530
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We'll be all right.

725
00:45:50,580 --> 00:45:53,770
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We're gathering food for when the warriors arrive.

726
00:45:53,810 --> 00:45:54,970
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't go far.

727
00:45:55,010 --> 00:45:56,740
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Now is not the time to be running off.

728
00:45:56,780 --> 00:45:58,410
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes, Father.

729
00:45:59,890 --> 00:46:02,320
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}When I see you wear that necklace...

730
00:46:02,360 --> 00:46:05,050
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}you look just like your mother.

731
00:46:05,090 --> 00:46:06,650
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I miss her.

732
00:46:06,690 --> 00:46:09,060
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But she is still with us.

733
00:46:09,100 --> 00:46:11,560
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Whenever the wind moves through the trees...

734
00:46:11,600 --> 00:46:13,330
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I feel her presence.

735
00:46:13,370 --> 00:46:16,300
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Our people looked to her for wisdom and strength.

736
00:46:16,340 --> 00:46:19,070
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Someday, they will look to you as well.

737
00:46:19,110 --> 00:46:21,940
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I would be honoured by that.

738
00:46:21,980 --> 00:46:23,740
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You shouldn't be out here alone.

739
00:46:23,780 --> 00:46:25,940
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'll send for Kocoum.

740
00:46:25,980 --> 00:46:27,470
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All right. What is it?

741
00:46:27,510 --> 00:46:28,980
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- What? - You're hiding something.

742
00:46:29,020 --> 00:46:30,950
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm not hiding anything.

743
00:46:30,980 --> 00:46:33,150
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas, you can tell me. I promise

744
00:46:33,190 --> 00:46:37,180
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I won't tell anyone... Pocahontas, look!

745
00:46:40,630 --> 00:46:42,090
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's one of them! I'm going to get...

746
00:46:42,130 --> 00:46:44,320
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What are you doing here?

747
00:46:44,360 --> 00:46:46,360
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I had to see you again.

748
00:46:46,400 --> 00:46:48,090
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas!

749
00:46:48,130 --> 00:46:49,600
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas!

750
00:46:49,640 --> 00:46:51,470
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Please! Don't say anything.

751
00:46:51,500 --> 00:46:53,130
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Quick! this way!

752
00:46:53,170 --> 00:46:54,700
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- But... - Nakoma.

753
00:46:54,740 --> 00:46:56,440
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Where is Pocahontas?

754
00:46:56,480 --> 00:46:59,270
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I... I haven't seen her.

755
00:46:59,310 --> 00:47:02,440
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas can't keep running off.

756
00:47:02,480 --> 00:47:04,310
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's dangerous out there.

757
00:47:04,350 --> 00:47:07,750
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Tell her that. She listens to you.

758
00:47:09,090 --> 00:47:11,890
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Huh! Sure she does.

759
00:47:27,310 --> 00:47:30,040
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This place is incredible.

760
00:47:30,080 --> 00:47:31,340
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And to think we came all this way...

761
00:47:31,380 --> 00:47:32,640
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}just to dig it up for gold.

762
00:47:32,680 --> 00:47:34,170
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Gold?

763
00:47:34,210 --> 00:47:36,880
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Hey, Meeko. - What's gold?

764
00:47:36,920 --> 00:47:38,980
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You know, it's, uh... it's, it's yellow.

765
00:47:39,020 --> 00:47:41,380
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It comes out of the ground. It's really valuable.

766
00:47:41,420 --> 00:47:43,360
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh! Here, we have lots of it.

767
00:47:43,390 --> 00:47:45,720
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Gold.

768
00:47:45,760 --> 00:47:49,560
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No No! Gold is this.

769
00:47:49,600 --> 00:47:52,220
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There's nothing like that around here.

770
00:47:52,270 --> 00:47:54,890
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- No gold? - Not that I've seen.

771
00:47:54,930 --> 00:47:57,730
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All this way for nothing.

772
00:47:57,770 --> 00:48:00,570
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, those boys are in for a big surprise.

773
00:48:00,610 --> 00:48:03,010
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Will they leave? - Some of them might.

774
00:48:05,210 --> 00:48:06,510
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Will you go home?

775
00:48:06,550 --> 00:48:10,070
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, it's not like I have much of a home to go back to.

776
00:48:10,120 --> 00:48:12,520
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I've never really belonged anywhere.

777
00:48:12,550 --> 00:48:15,350
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You could belong here.

778
00:48:23,500 --> 00:48:25,430
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What was that?!

779
00:48:25,470 --> 00:48:26,930
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Did you see something?

780
00:48:26,970 --> 00:48:29,870
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No. No. I just, uh... I...

781
00:48:29,900 --> 00:48:33,170
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I didn't see anything, did I?

782
00:48:33,210 --> 00:48:34,700
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look again.

783
00:48:35,980 --> 00:48:38,710
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Let it break upon you #

784
00:48:38,750 --> 00:48:44,380
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}# Like a wave upon the sand #

785
00:48:44,420 --> 00:48:47,390
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Hello, John Smith.

786
00:48:47,420 --> 00:48:50,320
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas, that tree is talking to me.

787
00:48:50,360 --> 00:48:52,590
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Then you should talk back.

788
00:48:52,630 --> 00:48:54,560
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't be frightened, young man.

789
00:48:54,590 --> 00:48:57,500
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}My bark is worse than my bite.

790
00:48:58,870 --> 00:49:00,590
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Say something.

791
00:49:00,630 --> 00:49:02,620
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What do you say to a tree?

792
00:49:02,670 --> 00:49:04,660
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Anything you want.

793
00:49:08,240 --> 00:49:09,540
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So, uh...

794
00:49:09,580 --> 00:49:13,170
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come closer, John Smith.

795
00:49:13,210 --> 00:49:15,810
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He has a good soul.

796
00:49:15,850 --> 00:49:17,610
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And he's handsome too!

797
00:49:17,650 --> 00:49:21,050
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Oh, I like her. - I knew you would.

798
00:49:21,090 --> 00:49:22,320
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Smith!

799
00:49:22,360 --> 00:49:24,620
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Smith Where are you, mate?

800
00:49:24,660 --> 00:49:25,850
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We can't let them see us.

801
00:49:25,890 --> 00:49:27,330
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Quick! Over here.

802
00:49:27,360 --> 00:49:29,120
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This place gives me the creeps.

803
00:49:29,160 --> 00:49:31,220
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Savages could be hiding anywhere.

804
00:49:31,260 --> 00:49:36,200
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Aye. Well, if you spot one, don't ask questions. Just shoot.

805
00:49:37,540 --> 00:49:39,370
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Watch your feet, you big oaf!

806
00:49:39,410 --> 00:49:41,200
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It wasn't me. It was the tree.

807
00:49:41,240 --> 00:49:42,400
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, of course!

808
00:49:42,440 --> 00:49:44,880
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The tree just felt like lifting its roots and...

809
00:49:48,250 --> 00:49:49,650
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Let's get out of here.

810
00:49:51,180 --> 00:49:52,810
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Ow! Run! - Ow!

811
00:49:52,850 --> 00:49:54,320
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But what about Smith?

812
00:49:54,350 --> 00:49:57,190
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He's a big lad. He can take care of himself.

813
00:49:57,220 --> 00:49:58,520
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm glad you're on our side.

814
00:49:58,560 --> 00:50:01,620
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There's still some snap in these old vines.

815
00:50:01,660 --> 00:50:04,390
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'd better get back before they send the whole camp out after me.

816
00:50:04,430 --> 00:50:06,130
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}When will I see you again?

817
00:50:06,170 --> 00:50:08,430
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Meet me tonight. Right here.

818
00:50:13,510 --> 00:50:18,310
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Well, I haven't had this much excitement in 200 years.

819
00:50:18,340 --> 00:50:21,470
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What am I doing? I shouldn't be seeing him again.

820
00:50:21,510 --> 00:50:23,510
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I mean, I want to see him again.

821
00:50:23,550 --> 00:50:26,640
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Who wouldn't? I want to see him again.

822
00:50:26,690 --> 00:50:28,520
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But still, something inside...

823
00:50:28,550 --> 00:50:30,650
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}is telling me it's the right thing.

824
00:50:30,690 --> 00:50:32,390
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Perhaps it's your dream.

825
00:50:32,430 --> 00:50:35,120
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}My dream? Do you think he's the one...

826
00:50:35,160 --> 00:50:37,530
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}the spinning arrow was pointing to?

827
00:50:46,910 --> 00:50:48,430
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The warriors are here!

828
00:51:00,020 --> 00:51:03,150
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas, are you crazy? What were you doing with one of them?

829
00:51:03,190 --> 00:51:04,550
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- There you are. - Kocoum!

830
00:51:04,590 --> 00:51:06,750
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look at them! Now we have enough warriors...

831
00:51:06,790 --> 00:51:09,130
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}to destroy those white demons!

832
00:51:10,660 --> 00:51:12,890
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Now that we are joined by our brothers...

833
00:51:12,930 --> 00:51:14,990
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}we will defeat this enemy.

834
00:51:22,440 --> 00:51:24,340
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Father, I need to speak with you.

835
00:51:24,380 --> 00:51:26,850
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Not now, my daughter. The council is gathering.

836
00:51:26,880 --> 00:51:30,410
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We don't have to fight them! There must be a better way.

837
00:51:30,450 --> 00:51:33,210
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Sometimes our paths are chosen for us.

838
00:51:33,250 --> 00:51:35,780
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But maybe we should try talking to them.

839
00:51:35,820 --> 00:51:37,480
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They do not want to talk.

840
00:51:37,520 --> 00:51:39,550
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But if one of them did want to talk...

841
00:51:39,590 --> 00:51:41,320
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}you would listen to him, wouldn't you?

842
00:51:41,360 --> 00:51:43,420
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Pocahontas. - Wouldn't you?

843
00:51:43,460 --> 00:51:47,760
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Of course I would. But it is not that simple.

844
00:51:47,800 --> 00:51:50,200
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Nothing is simple any more.

845
00:52:34,150 --> 00:52:37,450
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Easy, Thomas. It's me.

846
00:52:37,480 --> 00:52:40,280
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, John. I could've killed you.

847
00:52:40,320 --> 00:52:42,220
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Not aiming like that, you couldn't.

848
00:52:42,260 --> 00:52:43,980
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Keep both eyes open when you shoot.

849
00:52:44,020 --> 00:52:45,920
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You'll see twice as well.

850
00:52:45,960 --> 00:52:48,430
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Smith, there you are!

851
00:52:48,460 --> 00:52:50,220
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We were looking all over for you.

852
00:52:50,260 --> 00:52:53,490
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Smith! Where have you been?

853
00:52:53,530 --> 00:52:56,300
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I was out scouting the terrain, sir.

854
00:52:56,340 --> 00:52:58,700
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Excellent. Then you must know the Indians' whereabouts.

855
00:52:58,740 --> 00:53:00,330
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We'll need that information for the battle.

856
00:53:00,370 --> 00:53:01,570
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What battle?

857
00:53:01,610 --> 00:53:04,580
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}We will eliminate these savages once and for all.

858
00:53:04,610 --> 00:53:06,080
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No! You can't do that!

859
00:53:06,110 --> 00:53:08,980
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, can't I?

860
00:53:09,020 --> 00:53:11,510
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Look, we don't have to fight them.

861
00:53:11,550 --> 00:53:13,820
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- John, what's gotten into you? - I met one of them.

862
00:53:13,850 --> 00:53:16,340
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- You what?! - A savage?

863
00:53:16,390 --> 00:53:19,050
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They're not savages. They can help us.

864
00:53:19,090 --> 00:53:20,250
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They know the land.

865
00:53:20,290 --> 00:53:21,560
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They know how to navigate the rivers.

866
00:53:23,260 --> 00:53:25,360
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- And look. It's food. - What is it?

867
00:53:25,400 --> 00:53:27,960
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's better than hardtack and gruel, that's for sure.

868
00:53:28,000 --> 00:53:29,190
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I like gruel.

869
00:53:29,240 --> 00:53:31,640
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They don't want to feed us, you ninnies!

870
00:53:31,670 --> 00:53:34,470
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They want to kill us! All of us!

871
00:53:34,510 --> 00:53:35,740
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They've got our gold...

872
00:53:35,780 --> 00:53:37,500
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and they'll do anything to keep it!

873
00:53:37,540 --> 00:53:39,030
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But there is no gold.

874
00:53:39,080 --> 00:53:41,050
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}No gold?

875
00:53:41,080 --> 00:53:45,410
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And I suppose your little Indian friend told you this?

876
00:53:45,450 --> 00:53:46,920
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes.

877
00:53:46,950 --> 00:53:50,550
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Lies! Lies! All of it! Murderous thieves!

878
00:53:50,590 --> 00:53:52,820
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}There's no room for their kind in civilized society.

879
00:53:52,860 --> 00:53:54,290
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But this is their land!

880
00:53:54,330 --> 00:53:57,730
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}This is my land! I make the laws here.

881
00:53:57,760 --> 00:54:02,060
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And I say anyone who so much as looks at an Indian...

882
00:54:02,100 --> 00:54:03,660
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}without killing him on sight...

883
00:54:03,700 --> 00:54:07,900
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}will be tried for treason and hanged!

884
00:54:12,590 --> 00:54:13,890
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas!

885
00:54:13,920 --> 00:54:15,860
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Nakoma! - Don't go out there.

886
00:54:15,890 --> 00:54:19,220
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I lied for you once. Don't ask me to do it again.

887
00:54:19,260 --> 00:54:20,730
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I have to do this.

888
00:54:20,760 --> 00:54:22,960
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- He's one of them! - You don't know him.

889
00:54:23,000 --> 00:54:24,160
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}If you go out there...

890
00:54:24,200 --> 00:54:26,030
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You'll be turning your back on your own people.

891
00:54:26,070 --> 00:54:28,470
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm trying to help my people.

892
00:54:28,500 --> 00:54:32,030
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas, please. You're my best friend.

893
00:54:32,070 --> 00:54:33,600
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I don't want you to get hurt.

894
00:54:33,640 --> 00:54:35,610
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I won't. I know what I'm doing.

895
00:54:35,640 --> 00:54:38,200
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas, no!

896
00:54:43,720 --> 00:54:45,080
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Ratcliffe wouldn't take us...

897
00:54:45,120 --> 00:54:46,850
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}halfway around the world for nothin'.

898
00:54:46,890 --> 00:54:48,650
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But what if Smith is right?

899
00:54:48,690 --> 00:54:50,590
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What if there is no gold?

900
00:54:50,630 --> 00:54:51,890
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}If you ask me...

901
00:54:51,930 --> 00:54:53,790
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Ratcliffe's been lying to us since we left London.

902
00:54:53,830 --> 00:54:55,760
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Listen to you, ya bunch of idiots.

903
00:54:55,800 --> 00:54:58,130
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Those savages didn't attack us for nothin'.

904
00:54:58,170 --> 00:55:00,030
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They're hidin' somethin'.

905
00:55:00,070 --> 00:55:01,700
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}If they do have the gold...

906
00:55:01,740 --> 00:55:03,530
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I reckon we'll have to fight 'em.

907
00:55:03,570 --> 00:55:06,200
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Either too hot or too cool.

908
00:55:06,240 --> 00:55:09,510
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I haven't been comfortable since we got here.

909
00:55:09,550 --> 00:55:13,350
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, I know. I've been itching a lot.

910
00:55:19,490 --> 00:55:22,010
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Follow him. - Yes, Governor.

911
00:55:22,060 --> 00:55:23,990
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I want to know where he's sneaking off to.

912
00:55:24,030 --> 00:55:25,190
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Yes, sir.

913
00:55:25,230 --> 00:55:28,460
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And if you happen to see any Indians,

914
00:55:28,500 --> 00:55:30,090
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Shoot them.

915
00:55:33,870 --> 00:55:36,600
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Oh, and Thomas, you've been a slipshod sailor

916
00:55:36,640 --> 00:55:39,270
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}and a poor excuse for a soldier.

917
00:55:39,310 --> 00:55:41,470
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't disappoint me again.

918
00:55:51,090 --> 00:55:53,650
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Kocoum. - What is it?

919
00:55:53,690 --> 00:55:55,780
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's Pocahontas.

920
00:55:55,820 --> 00:55:58,550
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What's wrong? Is she all right?

921
00:56:00,600 --> 00:56:02,590
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I think she's in trouble.

922
00:56:07,040 --> 00:56:10,130
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The Earth is trembling, child. What's happened?

923
00:56:10,170 --> 00:56:11,610
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The warriors are here!

924
00:56:11,640 --> 00:56:14,770
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Pocahontas! - John!

925
00:56:14,810 --> 00:56:16,240
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Listen to me.

926
00:56:16,280 --> 00:56:18,640
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}My men are planning to attack your people.

927
00:56:18,680 --> 00:56:19,840
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You've got to warn them.

928
00:56:19,880 --> 00:56:22,350
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Maybe it's not too late to stop this.

929
00:56:22,380 --> 00:56:24,320
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You have to come with me and talk to my father.

930
00:56:24,350 --> 00:56:27,080
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas, talking isn't going to do any good.

931
00:56:27,120 --> 00:56:28,920
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I already tried talking to my men...

932
00:56:28,960 --> 00:56:31,050
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}but everything about this land has them spooked.

933
00:56:35,730 --> 00:56:38,200
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}That's the strangest creature I've ever seen.

934
00:56:42,240 --> 00:56:43,860
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Percy?!

935
00:56:45,340 --> 00:56:47,810
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Easy, Percy! Come here!

936
00:56:47,840 --> 00:56:49,040
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Meeko, come back!

937
00:56:49,080 --> 00:56:50,540
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You see what I mean?

938
00:56:50,580 --> 00:56:51,880
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Once two sides want to fight, nothing can stop them.

939
00:56:51,910 --> 00:56:53,310
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come Come here, both of you!

940
00:56:53,350 --> 00:56:55,210
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's all right! It's all right! He's a friend!

941
00:56:55,250 --> 00:56:56,550
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Bad! Bad dog! Sit!

942
00:56:58,820 --> 00:57:01,650
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- What are you doing? Meeko! - Percy, get back here!

943
00:57:01,690 --> 00:57:02,990
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What are you doing? Stop that!

944
00:57:03,030 --> 00:57:05,520
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All right, that's enough!

945
00:57:12,500 --> 00:57:14,830
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}It's enough to make your sap boil.

946
00:57:16,510 --> 00:57:20,970
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Now then, there's something I want to show you. Look.

947
00:57:24,750 --> 00:57:25,970
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}The ripples.

948
00:57:26,980 --> 00:57:28,210
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}What about them?

949
00:57:28,250 --> 00:57:30,340
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}So small at first,

950
00:57:30,390 --> 00:57:34,050
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}then look how they grow.

951
00:57:34,090 --> 00:57:36,820
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But someone has to start them.

952
00:57:36,860 --> 00:57:39,330
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}They're not going to listen to us.

953
00:57:39,360 --> 00:57:41,660
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Young man, sometimes the right path

954
00:57:41,700 --> 00:57:43,490
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}is not the easiest one.

955
00:57:43,530 --> 00:57:47,530
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Don't you see? Only when the fighting stops...

956
00:57:47,570 --> 00:57:50,560
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}can you be together.

957
00:57:53,440 --> 00:57:56,430
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All right. Let's go talk to your father.

958
00:58:32,610 --> 00:58:34,910
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kocoum! No!

959
00:58:40,790 --> 00:58:41,980
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kocoum!

960
00:58:46,160 --> 00:58:49,960
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Leave him alone!

961
00:59:03,850 --> 00:59:05,940
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kocoum! Stop!

962
00:59:08,280 --> 00:59:11,280
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Both eyes open.

963
00:59:18,060 --> 00:59:21,460
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- Thomas! - Is he...

964
00:59:21,500 --> 00:59:23,360
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You killed him.

965
00:59:23,400 --> 00:59:25,370
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}- I thought that... - Get away from him!

966
00:59:25,400 --> 00:59:27,490
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas, it won't help! He was only...

967
00:59:27,540 --> 00:59:28,800
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}He killed him!

968
00:59:32,010 --> 00:59:34,640
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Thomas, get out of here!

969
00:59:34,680 --> 00:59:37,010
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Get out of here!

970
01:00:39,040 --> 01:00:41,010
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Who did this?

971
01:00:41,040 --> 01:00:43,140
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas was out in the woods.

972
01:00:43,180 --> 01:00:47,840
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kocoum went to find her and this white man attacked him.

973
01:00:47,880 --> 01:00:50,280
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Your weapons are strong,

974
01:00:50,320 --> 01:00:53,050
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}but now our anger is stronger.

975
01:00:53,090 --> 01:00:55,890
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}At sunrise he will be the first to die!

976
01:00:55,920 --> 01:00:57,080
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}But, Father...

977
01:00:57,130 --> 01:01:00,120
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I told you to stay in the village.

978
01:01:00,160 --> 01:01:02,100
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You disobeyed me.

979
01:01:02,130 --> 01:01:04,120
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}You have shamed your father!

980
01:01:04,170 --> 01:01:05,960
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I was only trying to help.

981
01:01:06,000 --> 01:01:10,060
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Because of your foolishness, Kocoum is dead!

982
01:01:10,110 --> 01:01:12,370
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Take him away!

983
01:01:26,220 --> 01:01:28,950
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Kocoum was just coming to protect me.

984
01:01:28,990 --> 01:01:30,820
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas...

985
01:01:30,860 --> 01:01:32,830
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I sent Kocoum after you.

986
01:01:34,360 --> 01:01:36,890
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I was worried about you.

987
01:01:36,930 --> 01:01:39,130
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I-I thought I was doing the right thing.

988
01:01:39,170 --> 01:01:42,600
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}All this happened because of me.

989
01:01:42,640 --> 01:01:47,170
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}And now I'll never see John Smith again.

990
01:01:47,210 --> 01:01:49,010
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Come with me.

991
01:01:53,620 --> 01:01:55,740
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas wants to look into the eyes...

992
01:01:55,780 --> 01:01:57,840
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}of the man who killed Kocoum.

993
01:02:00,420 --> 01:02:02,150
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Be quick.

994
01:02:19,710 --> 01:02:22,340
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}Pocahontas.

995
01:02:24,750 --> 01:02:26,770
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I'm so sorry.

996
01:02:26,820 --> 01:02:28,280
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}For what? This?

997
01:02:28,320 --> 01:02:30,650
{\fnCandara\bord1\shad1\1c&H45DFEC&\b0\i1}I've gotten out of worse scrapes than this.

998
01:02:30,690 --> 01:02:32,620
